cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the applicability of educational data mining in Afghanistan's education system, which involves analyzing and processing large amounts of data to improve educational processes. This falls under the category of computational science (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of data storage and processing, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of online questionnaires and data analysis to gather information, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for using data mining to predict student attrition and select proper fields of study, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
